name: Gold Enamel Cuff Red and Smoke
description:
A great new find from Australia. 

This bold cuff exudes sophisticated simplicity. It adds a fabulous, glossy colour pop to winter dressing. Gold plated, and with high quality enamel, this is a very special piece. In red and smoke.

Designed with a colour block on each half, this bangle is 3cm wide with a convenient  and solid hinge opening. This is so easy to wear.

name: Unreal Fur Thread Through Faux Fur Stole
description:
Grazia Magazine (issue 451, November 2013) says "Thanks to a couple of choice brands excelling in the stuff, fake has never looked so fabulous…Unreal Fur has the market cornered." We couldn't agree more, this is really a gorgeous stole.

The Saturday Telegraph Magazine fashion feature 24/11/13 suggests the Unreal Fur fur-ocious stole as a great way to add interest to a L.B.D. 

Designed and made in Australia by Unreal Fur, a brand which is new to the UK and is clearly making a real impact this year, for good reason. We are both hoping for one of these under the tree.

name: Tse-Tse French Gold Glazed Porcelain Bowl
description:
Striking a careful balance between sophistication and fun, the undulating lines of these bowls are really unusual.  Designed in Paris by a pair of talented young designers and hand made in traditional porcelain moulds in Hungary.  The care and attention to detail in the design and creation shines through in the 'famished' bowls.  

The outside of the porcelain is finished in a clear glaze and the inside is glazed in gold. Fill with smarties or twiglets for a gorgeous addition to your canapés.  This would make a fabulous hostess present. 

Dimensions: Height 7 cm (2,8 in), Ø 13 cm (5,1 in)

name: Simpatico Reindeer Candle
description:
The Simpatico reindeer candle is classic Christmas. The red and white packaging is Nordic in its understated simplicity. Simpatico is a family company based in Northern Michigan in the US, where there is a strong Scandinavian influence. 

A simple blend of vegetable wax and fragrance allows nature-inspired scents to carry throughout your space. This 100% vegetable wax blend is made from renewable sources and is grown by American farmers.  They are hand poured into a thick, tapered glass and packaged in a decorative gift box.  Made with a cotton wick, they burn approximately 40 hours.

Inspired by vintage botanical books, field guides and fragrances reminiscent of simpler days gone by.  The Reindeer candle has red currants and cranberries colliding with cedar wood, fir and embers.

name: Jet Set Bag
description:
This clear and black patent leather bag has two zipped compartments and is a perfect present for all the frequent fliers we know.  

We love the slick black patent edging on this clear bag, perfect for prettying up the rigours of airport security.  We will be packing this in our hand luggage for our next big trip but it is just the right size for weekends away also.  

It is designed to organise liquids, gels and travel accessories. Or great for keeping headphones, pens, flight socks, face cream, lavender spritz, hair bands or medicines in it for easy access during travel.  No more searching round the bottom of your travel bag for that essential item, we've all been there...

Also excellent for use in a gym bag, for packing chargers and cables or as a make-up or travel wash bag.

Measures 18cm x 12cm x 5cm

name: Ayala Bar Cross Pendant Necklace
description:
We are fortunate to have a few necklaces from the current season designed and hand made by the jeweller Ayala Bar, favourite of stylish hotel designer Kit Kemp.  Each one feels like a piece of art carefully crafted in lush colours and materials. We only have one of each style available.

This gorgeous cross is 5cm tall and 3.25cm wide and the chain is adjustable between 48 and 56cm in length or 18-20 inches.

The necklaces are characterized by mosaic-like work and ornate surface patterns. Each piece is analogous to a miniature painting. Richly colored stones embedded into custom-made fittings combine to create a striking impression.  Unexpected materials have been matched to create eye-catching adornments which incorporate handwoven beads, satiny finishes, lush velvets and polished gems.

Ayala Bar limits her collection run to six months. Thereafter, she combines different colours, beads, fabrics and shapes to create a brand new collection. She does not repeat her designs, so the pieces are very collectable.

name: Handmade Glass Decoupage Trinket Tray
description:
Handmade and designed in Bridie Hall's London studio, this is a collectable piece, perfect for your weekend hosts. This tray measures 8" by 10", just the right size for a mantelpiece or for letters or keys on the hall table. Perfect on a chest of drawers for cufflinks or change. 'Sitting on the Edge of the Jungle', India 1840 has a cool, classic colonial feel, epitomising the faded glory of the Raj. 

The tray is backed with a lacquered 18th century map of London, denoting the origin of production. Bridie Hall collects antique images which are reprinted and pieced together in layers under glass. 

Bridie Hall’s contemporary take on the ancient practice of decoupage, has resulted in unique decorative plates that are individually created. Hall obtains her diverse range decoupage images from antique stores and archival sources around the UK, which reflect eclectic themes linked by her fascination of natural history, old maps and imagery of London.

Wipe clean only, do not submerge in water.
